# Reverse an Array

## Problem
Reverse the given array.

## Approach
Use Two Pointer Approach.
- i starts from the beginning.
- j starts from the end.
- Swap both elements.
- Move both pointers towards the center.

## Algorithm
1. Initialize i = 0 and j = n - 1.
2. While i < j:
   - Swap arr[i] and arr[j].
   - i++
   - j--
3. Array is reversed.

## Java Code

```java
class Solution {
    public void reverseArray(int arr[]) {

        int i = 0;
        int j = arr.length - 1;

        while (i < j) {
            int temp = arr[i];
            arr[i] = arr[j];
            arr[j] = temp;

            i++;
            j--;
        }
    }
}
